{"title_page": "Haryana Institute of Civil Aviation", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2017}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=December 2017}}\n{{Infobox Indian state government\n|name_of_state= Haryana\n|coat_of_arms= \n|state_flag=\n|name_of_governor= [[Kaptan Singh Solanki]]\n|name_of_chief_minister= [[Manohar Lal Khattar]]\n|name_of_dpy_chief_minister= [[Abhimanyu Sindhu|Captain Abhimanyu Singh Sindhu]]\n|legislative_assembly= [[Haryana Vidhan Sabha]]\n|speaker= \n|legislative_council=\n|chairman=\n|high_court= [[Punjab and Haryana High Court]]\n|chief_justice= Ashutosh Mohunta (acting)\n|website={{url|http://haryana.gov.in/}}\n}}\n\nThe '''Haryana Institute of Civil Aviation''' ('''HICA''') is a [[Government of Haryana]] undertaking that operates 3 flying clubs in the state of [[Haryana]] to impart pilot training.<ref>[http://haraviation.gov.in Haryana Institute of Aviation]</ref><ref>[http://haryana.gov.in/ Haryana Govt]</ref>\n\nThe current minister for the 2014-2019 term is [[Ram Bilas Sharma]].\n\n==Flying clubs==\n{{see also | History_of_Haryana#Aviation | label 1 = Aviation history of Haryana | List_of_airports_in_India#Haryana | label 2 = List of airports in India }}\n\nThe Haryana Institute of Civil Aviation operates the following 3 flying clubs providing [[flight training]] for aspiring [[Pilot (aeronautics)|pilot]]s.<ref>[http://haraviation.gov.in/docs/prospectus.pdf Haryana Institute of Aviation] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140928160629/http://haraviation.gov.in/docs/prospectus.pdf |date=2014-09-28 }} Prospectus, page 5</ref>\n\n* [[Hisar Airport#Hisar Aviation Club|Hisar Aviation Club]] at [[Hisar Airport]]: As of July 2016, Hisar based Aviation flying club had two aircraft, a 4-seater Cessna 172 built in 2008 and an old 2-seater Cessna 152 built in 1986. The institutes has 15 approved seats to impart training for the [[commercial pilot licence]] (CPL) and [[private pilot licence]] (PPL). The CPL requires a minimum of 200 hours flying experience.<ref name=trib2>[http://www.tribuneindia.com/news/sunday-special/kaleidoscope/haryana-flies-mostly-on-paper/260323.html Haryana flies mostly on paper, The Tribune,  Published on 3 July 2016]</ref> In September 2019, [[Spice Jet]] also started a flight training academy at Hisar airport with 10 training aircraft to train 100 pilots every year.<ref>[https://english.newstracklive.com/news/cm-manohar-lal-khattar-inaugurates-hisar-airport-of-haryana-mc23-nu-1033197-1.html Haryana CM ML Khattar inaugurates flight services from Hisar Airport], NewstrackLive, 3 Sept 2019.</ref> 4 girls with state domicile and 10% students with Haryana domicile will get 50% waiver on tuition fee, SpiceJet will place 70% of the 100 pilot trainees within its own organisation.<ref name=expand1>[https://www.indiatoday.in/india/story/haryana-cm-launches-udan-regional-connectivity-scheme-1594784-2019-09-03 Haryana CM launches UDAN regional connectivity scheme], [[India Today]], 3 Sept 2019.</ref>\n* [[Kalka Airport#Pinjore Aviation Club|Pinjore Aviation Club]] at [[Kalka Airport]]\n* [[Karnal Airport#Karnal Flying Club|Karnal Flying Club]] at [[Karnal Airport]]\n\n==Pilot License Courses offered==\nThe HICA offers flying training and preparation courses to pilots for the following [[Directorate General of Civil Aviation (India)|Directorate General of Civil Aviation]] licenses':<ref>[http://haraviation.gov.in/docs/prospectus.pdf Haryana Institute of Aviation] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140928160629/http://haraviation.gov.in/docs/prospectus.pdf |date=2014-09-28 }} Prospectus</ref>\n* [[Student pilot certificate|Student pilot license]]\n* [[Private pilot licence]]\n* [[Commercial pilot license]]\n* [[Glider pilot license]]\n\nThe Government of Haryana provides subsidies for the above to the natives of the state of Haryana who must apply for it using a [[Domicile (law)|Haryana Domicile Certificate]].\n\n== See also ==\n* [[List of schools in Hisar]]\n* [[List of universities and colleges in Hisar]]\n* [[List of institutions of higher education in Haryana]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n{{Airports in India}}\n{{Haryana}}\n\n{{coord missing|Haryana}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Aviation schools in Haryana]]\n[[Category:Government of Haryana|Institute of Civil Aviation]]\n[[Category:Universities and colleges in Haryana]]\n[[Category:Universities and colleges in Hisar (city)]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2017}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=December 2017}}\n{{Infobox Indian state government\n|name_of_state= Haryana\n|coat_of_arms= \n|state_flag=\n|name_of_governor= [[Kaptan Singh Solanki]]\n|name_of_chief_minister= [[Manohar Lal Khattar]]\n|name_of_dpy_chief_minister= [[Abhimanyu Sindhu|Captain Abhimanyu Singh Sindhu]]\n|legislative_assembly= [[Haryana Vidhan Sabha]]\n|speaker= \n|legislative_council=\n|chairman=\n|high_court= [[Punjab and Haryana High Court]]\n|chief_justice= Ashutosh Mohunta (acting)\n|website={{url|http://haryana.gov.in/}}\n}}\n\nThe '''Haryana Institute of Civil Aviation''' ('''HICA''') is a [[Government of Haryana]] undertaking that operates 3 flying clubs in the state of [[Haryana]] to impart pilot training.<ref>[http://haraviation.gov.in Haryana Institute of Aviation]</ref><ref>[http://haryana.gov.in/ Haryana Govt]</ref>\n\nThe current minister for the 2014-2019 term is [[Ram Bilas Sharma]].\n\n==Flying clubs==\n{{see also | History_of_Haryana#Aviation | label 1 = Aviation history of Haryana | List_of_airports_in_India#Haryana | label 2 = List of airports in India }}\n\nThe Haryana Institute of Civil Aviation operates the following 3 flying clubs providing [[flight training]] for aspiring [[Pilot (aeronautics)|pilot]]s.<ref>[http://haraviation.gov.in/docs/prospectus.pdf Haryana Institute of Aviation] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140928160629/http://haraviation.gov.in/docs/prospectus.pdf |date=2014-09-28 }} Prospectus, page 5</ref>\n\n* [[Hisar_Airport#Hisar_